items.name: B-Horror (~ Japanese Victorian Gothic)
items.description:
V2.0

Two gothic/gothic lolita text inversions

  • b_horror_v2_1 is cute and dressy, good for gothic lolita and cute vampires

  • b_horror_v2_2 is dark, good for scary vampires

Prompt:

  • nsfw

  • backlight (all the training samples have a girl dressed in black with a very bright moon or a very bright window)

  • colorless (most drawings have low contrast or low saturation)

Other notes:

  • this was difficult to train, mostly because all source drawings have low contrast, low saturation, lots of small elements that turn into artifacts, and because most girls have a black corset, the waist area is always excessively dark/shadowed

  • correcting brightness/contract, maybe this: https://civitai.com/articles/1125/new-tool-cdcolordetail-tuner

  • therefore, a good way to make a drawing without the text inversion is to add "victorian dress, frills, backlight, low contrast, low saturation, 90's style manga" to the prompt

  • the model has a tendency to:

    • make girls that hold things in their hands (their dress, cake, flowers, a glass of blood)

    • add some chibi clones (sometimes)

V1.0-Experimental

I was doing sth with the computer, and this appeared.

You need to play with CFG scale, embedding strength, and strength of 'nsfw' in the negative.

Embeddings:

  • b_horror_1: vampire, red and black

  • b_horror_2: demon, pink and black, scary symmetry

  • b_horror_3: nsfw, lots of frills, good for goth lolita

Other notes:

  • horror_sth_3 is a mix of 20% horror1, 50% horror2, 30% horror3

  • I have included some images with latent upscale, you should try to obtain the same results by hand (it's something weird with how intermediate checkpoint examples are generated when training a text inversion)

items.name: Expressions Helper Realistic
items.description:
Expressions Helper Realistic is the outcome of an ambitious project that focuses on capturing real facial expressions. Trained for 10 epochs and 3830 steps, this AI model utilizes images from films and photographs of real individuals to help generate authentic expressions of disgust, surprise, sadness, anger, and fear. The model's weights vary for each expression and the models used, while the results are influenced by both positive and negative prompts. With its advanced algorithms and training, Expressions Helper Realistic Model offers a valuable tool to facilitate the creation of realistic and emotionally rich facial expressions, enhancing storytelling and creative projects.

The keyword is recommended to be inserted at the beginning of the prompt to have a more effective effect

Keywords :

  • angry

  • sad

  • surprised

  • scared

  • disgusted

With unrealistic styles the result is not guaranteed because the model has been trained only with realistic images, although this works more or less effectively on all styles.

Just try it!

items.name: Ruby Roundhouse from Jumanji movies (Karen Gillan)
items.description:
Although I have already trained a model based on that actress (Karen Gillan (Amy Pond on Dr Who TV show)), that one was focused on general purpose. This time I wanted to make a test, training only a character from a movie, a one I liked, and this is the result. Therefore I decided not to clasify it as a second version of the former one, but more as a character.

I think it is very good for positioning that character on different scenarios and a bit inflexible in terms of general purpose but with some effort, it could be possible. I hope you enjoy it.

Due to civitai's censorship, many full body images (that show typical suit of that caracter) won't be visible until you confirm that you are over a certain age.

This LyCORIS has been trained after carefully selecting 90 images, most of them screenshots from Jumanji movies. All photos have been enhanced to make the most of them. I hope you like it!

I don't ask for anything but any respectful constructive review (after having tested the model) would be highly appreciated or at least press Like if you're happy with results after trying it out! Thanks in advance and enjoy it!

From my experience it runs best with Edge Of Realism, pirsusEpicRealism, epicDiffusion, RealisticVision, CyberRealistic, Deliberate checkpoints, among others, although I think it will be just fine in other SD 1.5 models as well.

CFG scale should be between 4-7.

LyCORIS weights should be between 0.9-1.2

Notice: This free work is intended for art and illustration purposes of emergent technology and not intended nor' trained for making illicit images, as the author I've taken care to not use any private data in the training process or designed it for such purposes. By downloading this model you are agreeing with the aforementioned intent and that you will not use my work to create / share images of a potentially immoral and / or illegal nature.

items.name: Faye Grant
items.description:
Faye Grant is an American actress, mainly known for her role as Julie Parrish in the TV show V that aired in 1983.

This is a 130-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of extremely sexy (f4yegr4nt:0.99), a woman as a sexy student, (closeup portrait), hair upsweep updo, ({white|yellow|pink|blue} tight long sleeve turtleneck top), at a cantina sitting bar (masterpiece:1.5) (photorealistic:1.1) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin texture pores hairs:1.1) (intricate) (8k) (HDR) (wallpaper) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus)"

Info

raining with 192 images
Followed the manual form [ [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free ],
You can access to this guide in Suggested Resources section.

Recommended set up

Sampler: Euler a, DPM family series
Sampling steps: 20 or 25+
CFG Scale: 7
CLIP Skip: 2
*Do not use [restore face] on anime character!*

LoRA Weighting: [1 - 0.9], (1 - 0.65)

Baking Step:
0. Drafting (512 x 512 res to find your desired sketch)
1. Hires fix (txt2img: 768 x 768, 768 x 512, 512 x 768, or above res)
2. inpaint (img2img: refine some unwanted effect, [Euler a] with 50+ step)
3. Upscaling (img2img: res*2 with [ControlNet Tile] & Ultimate SD upscale)

Upscaler for [Step 1 - 3]: [R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B, 4x-AnimeSharp, 4x-UltraSharp]
I always skip Step 0, 2 :P

Basic prompts

TaigeiKC, (long sleeves) serafuku, (red) neckerchief, (blue) sailor collar, (whale print) white apron, (blue pleated skirt), (black) pantyhose, magatama

items.name: Lawrence Alma Tadema Style
items.description:
Lawrence Alma-Tadema (1836-1912) was a Dutch-born British painter who achieved great success during the late 19th and early 20th centuries. He is best known for his meticulously detailed and highly realistic depictions of scenes from antiquity.

Alma-Tadema's art often focused on ancient Roman and Greek civilizations, presenting idealized visions of their opulent lifestyles and leisurely pursuits. His works captured the minutest details of architecture, clothing, and artifacts, reflecting his extensive research and attention to historical accuracy.

The artist's paintings exude a sense of tranquility and serenity, often depicting scenes of elegant figures engaged in activities such as reading, playing music, or strolling through lush gardens. His use of light, color, and texture created a sense of warmth and inviting atmosphere.

Alma-Tadema's paintings showcased his mastery of technique, employing smooth brushwork and rich colors to render exquisite textures and intricate patterns. He had a keen eye for detail and a meticulous approach, which made his works highly sought after and admired.

During his lifetime, Alma-Tadema's art received widespread recognition and acclaim. He was a member of the Royal Academy of Arts and was honored with numerous awards and accolades. His paintings were highly sought after by collectors and were reproduced in popular publications of the time.

Although Alma-Tadema's popularity declined in the early 20th century with the rise of modernism, his works have experienced a resurgence of interest and appreciation in recent years. Today, his paintings continue to captivate audiences with their meticulous craftsmanship, evocative storytelling, and their ability to transport viewers to a bygone era of grandeur and elegance.

items.name: Leonid Afremov Style
items.description:
Leonid Afremov (1955-2019) was a Russian-Israeli artist known for his distinctive and vibrant oil paintings. He was celebrated for his unique style, often referred to as "Afremovian," which combined elements of Impressionism, Expressionism, and Post-Impressionism.

Afremov's artworks are characterized by their bold use of color, loose brushwork, and a sense of atmospheric beauty. His paintings often depict cityscapes, landscapes, and rainy scenes, capturing the essence of a moment and evoking an emotional response from viewers.

One of his notable techniques was the use of a palette knife, which added texture and depth to his paintings. This technique, combined with his fearless application of color, resulted in dynamic and visually striking compositions.

Afremov's subjects ranged from tranquil park scenes and charming European streets to bustling cityscapes and romantic seascapes. His paintings had a dreamlike quality, with the interplay of light and color creating a sense of enchantment and nostalgia.

The artist's use of vibrant and contrasting colors, such as bold blues, fiery oranges, and rich purples, contributed to the distinctive allure of his artworks. These hues added a sense of drama and heightened emotion, inviting viewers to immerse themselves in the scenes he painted.

Leonid Afremov's art achieved widespread popularity, with his paintings being collected and exhibited around the world. His ability to capture the essence of a moment, infuse it with emotion, and create a lasting impact on the viewer's senses is a testament to his skill as an artist.

Despite his passing in 2019, Afremov's legacy as a master of color and atmosphere lives on. His unique style and ability to transport viewers to vibrant and emotionally resonant scenes continue to inspire and captivate art enthusiasts around the globe.

items.name: Leonora Carrington Style
items.description:
Leonora Carrington (1917-2011) was a British-Mexican artist and writer who made significant contributions to the Surrealist movement. She is celebrated for her imaginative and often surreal artworks, which combined elements of fantasy, mythology, and the occult.

Carrington's art was characterized by its dreamlike quality and rich symbolism. Her paintings and sculptures often featured enigmatic and fantastical creatures, hybrid beings, and magical landscapes. She drew inspiration from various mythologies, folklore, and her own personal experiences, creating a world filled with mystery and enchantment.

Her distinctive style incorporated intricate details, bold colors, and a sense of whimsy. Carrington's works explored themes of transformation, identity, and the subconscious, reflecting her interest in psychology and the exploration of the human psyche.

Beyond her visual art, Carrington also excelled as a writer. She wrote numerous short stories, novels, and plays, often incorporating elements of fantasy and magic realism. Her writings, like her visual art, embraced themes of rebellion, liberation, and the exploration of alternative realities.

Carrington's art and writings challenged societal norms and traditional gender roles, reflecting her own rebellious and independent spirit. She was one of the few women associated with the Surrealist movement and played a vital role in expanding the possibilities of artistic expression.

In the later years of her life, Carrington settled in Mexico, where she continued to produce art and became an influential figure in the local art scene. Her contributions to the art world were recognized with numerous exhibitions and accolades.

Leonora Carrington's legacy as an artist and writer continues to inspire and captivate audiences. Her imaginative and fantastical works challenge our perceptions of reality and invite us into a world of symbolism, magic, and the subconscious. Her unique perspective and contributions have solidified her as a celebrated figure within the Surrealist movement and beyond.

items.name: Louis Comfort Tiffany Style
items.description:
Louis Comfort Tiffany (1848-1933) was an American artist and designer known for his contributions to the fields of stained glass, interior design, and decorative arts. He was one of the leading figures of the Art Nouveau movement in the late 19th and early 20th centuries.

Tiffany's most renowned works are his exquisite stained glass windows and lamps. He revolutionized the art of stained glass by experimenting with new techniques and materials, creating vibrant and intricate designs that showcased his mastery of color and light. His use of opalescent glass, which he patented, resulted in a unique iridescent effect that became a signature feature of his work.

In addition to stained glass, Tiffany also worked in other mediums, including glass mosaics, ceramics, jewelry, and metalwork. He was the founder of the Tiffany Studios, a design studio and workshop that produced a wide range of decorative objects, including lamps, vases, and furniture.

Tiffany's designs often incorporated organic and natural forms, inspired by the beauty of flowers, plants, and landscapes. He was also influenced by Asian art and design, particularly Japanese aesthetics, which he integrated into his works.

His designs were characterized by their attention to detail, meticulous craftsmanship, and a harmonious integration of materials. Tiffany embraced the concept of the Gesamtkunstwerk, or "total work of art," by creating cohesive environments where every element, from lighting to furnishings, worked together to create a unified and visually stunning space.

The artistic legacy of Louis Comfort Tiffany continues to captivate and inspire. His innovative techniques, bold use of color, and dedication to craftsmanship have left an indelible mark on the world of art and design. Tiffany's creations, with their timeless beauty and elegant aesthetics, continue to be celebrated and sought after by collectors and admirers worldwide.

items.name: Lovis Corinth Style
items.description:
Lovis Corinth (1858-1925) was a German painter and printmaker associated with the Berlin Secession movement and German Expressionism. He is recognized for his versatile artistic style, which evolved throughout his career, encompassing Realism, Impressionism, and Symbolism.

Corinth's early works reflected the influence of Realism, depicting scenes of everyday life and portraits with meticulous detail. Later, he transitioned to a more impressionistic style, employing loose brushwork and vibrant colors to capture the essence of a subject and convey atmospheric effects.

The artist's subject matter ranged from landscapes and still lifes to portraits and historical scenes. He was particularly known for his psychologically insightful portraits, which conveyed a sense of the sitter's personality and inner thoughts.

Corinth's art underwent a significant transformation following a stroke in 1911, which left him partially paralyzed. Despite this physical setback, he continued to create, and his style took on a more expressive and energetic quality. His later works displayed a heightened sense of emotion, marked by bold brushwork, vibrant colors, and a sense of urgency.

In addition to his paintings, Corinth was a skilled printmaker, creating etchings and lithographs with a distinctive graphic quality. He explored a wide range of themes and genres in his prints, often with a dark and introspective undertone.

Lovis Corinth's artistic contributions and innovative approach to painting have earned him a prominent place in the history of German art. His willingness to experiment with different styles and techniques, coupled with his keen psychological insight, set him apart as a significant figure in the development of German Expressionism.

Today, Corinth's works can be found in major art museums and collections around the world, and his legacy continues to be celebrated for its technical skill, emotional depth, and contribution to the diverse artistic landscape of the early 20th century.

items.name: Lucas Cranach Style
items.description:
Lucas Cranach the Elder (1472-1553) was a German painter and printmaker who played a significant role in the Northern Renaissance movement. He is best known for his distinctive style and his contributions to religious, mythological, and portrait painting.

Cranach's works often featured graceful figures, vibrant colors, and meticulous attention to detail. He was skilled at capturing the delicate nuances of the human form and imbuing his subjects with a sense of dignity and elegance.

As a court painter, Cranach was associated with the court of Elector Frederick the Wise of Saxony, where he produced numerous portraits of the ruling family and other notable figures. His portraits were highly sought after for their ability to capture the individuality and character of his subjects.

Cranach's religious paintings were influenced by the Reformation movement led by Martin Luther. He created numerous altarpieces and religious scenes that conveyed the teachings and beliefs of the Protestant Reformation, often with a focus on the figure of Christ and the Virgin Mary.

In addition to his religious and portrait paintings, Cranach was also known for his prints and woodcuts, which were widely circulated and influenced the development of the printmaking medium.

Cranach's art embodied the spirit of the Northern Renaissance, combining humanist ideals with a distinctive German aesthetic. His contributions to the art world, particularly his portraiture and his exploration of religious themes, continue to be celebrated and studied.

Lucas Cranach the Elder's legacy as a master of the Northern Renaissance endures, with his works showcased in major art museums and collections worldwide. His artistry, technical skill, and influence on the art of his time make him an important figure in the history of European art.

items.name: Luc Schuiten Style
items.description:
Luc Schuiten is a Belgian architect and artist known for his visionary and imaginative architectural designs and illustrations. Born in 1944, he is recognized for his unique approach that combines ecological principles, biomimicry, and a sense of wonder for the natural world.

Schuiten's architectural designs often feature organic shapes, flowing lines, and a harmonious integration with the environment. His buildings are inspired by nature and seek to create sustainable and regenerative spaces that blend seamlessly with their surroundings.

Through his intricate illustrations and concept art, Schuiten presents a vision of a future where cities coexist with nature in a harmonious balance. He envisions vertical gardens, green roofs, and sustainable transportation systems that prioritize the well-being of both people and the planet.

Schuiten's drawings are rich in detail, capturing the essence of his architectural ideas and allowing viewers to immerse themselves in his imagined worlds. His illustrations often depict fantastical cityscapes, lush landscapes, and futuristic transportation systems, creating a sense of awe and inspiration.

As an architect, Schuiten has completed several notable projects, including the Botanic Center in Brussels, Belgium, which showcases his innovative and sustainable design principles.

Luc Schuiten's work challenges traditional notions of architecture and invites us to reimagine our relationship with the built environment and the natural world. His visionary designs and illustrations inspire us to consider alternative ways of living and coexisting with nature, offering a glimpse into a more sustainable and harmonious future.

items.name: Lyonel Feininger Style
items.description:
Lyonel Feininger (1871-1956) was a German-American painter and printmaker associated with the Bauhaus movement and the Expressionist art movement. He was known for his unique blend of abstract and geometric forms, as well as his innovative approach to composition.

Feininger's early works were influenced by Impressionism and Post-Impressionism, characterized by their loose brushwork and vibrant colors. However, he soon transitioned to a more abstract style, inspired by the Cubist movement and his involvement with the Blue Rider group.

One of Feininger's notable contributions to the art world was his exploration of the relationship between art and music. He often sought to capture the rhythm and harmony of music in his visual compositions, creating paintings that exuded a sense of movement and musicality.

Feininger's works often featured architectural and industrial subjects, reflecting his fascination with urban landscapes and geometric forms. His paintings and prints showcased a keen attention to detail, as well as a sense of order and precision.

As a member of the Bauhaus, Feininger played a significant role in the development of modern art and design. He taught at the Bauhaus school in Weimar and later in Dessau, where he influenced a generation of artists with his innovative ideas and approaches.

Feininger's art received recognition both during his lifetime and posthumously. His works were exhibited internationally, and he was honored with numerous awards and retrospectives.

Lyonel Feininger's legacy as an artist continues to inspire and influence contemporary artists. His unique blend of abstraction, geometric forms, and musicality in his compositions made him a distinct voice in the modern art movement, and his contributions to the development of modern art remain significant.

items.name: Makoto Shinkai Style
items.description:
Makoto Shinkai is a Japanese animator, filmmaker, and writer known for his visually stunning and emotionally evocative anime films. Born in 1973, Shinkai gained international recognition for his works, which often explore themes of love, longing, and the human connection.

Shinkai's films are celebrated for their breathtaking animation, attention to detail, and intricate storytelling. He often weaves together elements of romance, science fiction, and fantasy to create narratives that captivate audiences and resonate on a deep emotional level.

One of his most renowned works is "Your Name" (Kimi no Na wa), released in 2016. The film became a global phenomenon, earning critical acclaim and commercial success. "Your Name" beautifully depicts a poignant tale of two young individuals who find themselves mysteriously connected through their dreams.

Shinkai's films are characterized by their stunning visuals, vibrant color palettes, and meticulous attention to natural landscapes and urban environments. His ability to capture the beauty of nature and its relationship with human experiences adds an extra layer of depth to his storytelling.

In addition to his talent as a filmmaker, Shinkai is also known for his skill as a writer. His scripts are poetic and introspective, delving into the complexities of human emotions and relationships. His narratives often touch upon universal themes such as loneliness, nostalgia, and the passage of time.

Makoto Shinkai's works have garnered widespread acclaim and have been influential in shaping the anime genre. His ability to transport audiences into captivating worlds and evoke genuine emotional responses has earned him a dedicated fan base worldwide.

As a filmmaker, Shinkai continues to explore new storytelling techniques and push the boundaries of animation. His films serve as a testament to the power of animation as a medium for storytelling, creating poignant and immersive experiences for viewers.
